postcontent:
Up for sale is a fully converted saiga with all the correct parts.  This is the harder to find 20" barrel model. This is an early import from Kalashnikov-USA.  Not sure how many of these were imported but it is very nice. It has a tapco G2 double hook trigger with a very crisp break.  Unlike most Saigas this one has the entire front end converted the correct way.  Besdies putting the correct front handguards on it, it also has an original gas block and the retainer for the front handguard.  It also has a threaded front sight block installed with an original half moon 74 break. An original russian optic has also been installed.  It is a PKS-01.  This is battle grade red dot that also has a black etched reticle so even if the batteries die you still have a black circle and dot. It sits to the left of center on the rifle so iron sights are also usable. I don't think theres a better red dot on the market, it has an incredibly wide field of view.  What makes Saiga rifles so good is they are the only AK's that still have the original barrels on them. Very low round count at 200-300. Included is sling, five 30 rnd mags and a 75 rnd drum. This is not a cheap AK, alot of work and money was put into it to turn it back into the weapon it was designed to be.

Price is $1500 for everything, I would sell just the rifle and 2 mags for $1000.

Face to Face only, no shipping.  Must be WI resident and legal to own firearms.
